result.execSummary:
The defendant Henry L McLemore was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Intimidate Victim/Use or Attempt Force [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments, Use of a Dangerous Weapon], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.45(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Must obey all rules and regulations while on probation.  Firearm prohibition warning given.

miscConds.notes: If supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.

Provide DNA sample as required by law and pay assessed surcharge.  Pay costs of supervision and court obligations.  No contact with M. McL until domestic violence program has been completed and contact is approved by agent and M.McL.  Cooperate with counseling, treatment and programs determined appropriate.  Follow through with recommendations.  Voting prohibited until sentence has been completed and civil rights are restored.

No use or possession of alcohol or controlled substances, except for those prescribed by treating health care provider.  Submit to random testing as required by agent.  Cooperate with AODA assessment and follow through with treatment, counseling and program recommendations, including aftercare programming.

timeConds.notes: Do not report to the jail late or under the influence of alcohol or controlled substances.

Ms. McClendon asks to be heard on bond. Mr. Repischak takes a moment to speak to the victim. Defense asks that bond be modified to $1000.00 cash. Defendant will live with his brother at 1241 Carlisle Ave, Racine, WI 53404. The State spoke with the victim and she indicated that it would be her preference that deft be released on even a signature bond. The victim does understand the no contact provision. The State, however, feels a significant amount of cash is appropriate citing the domestic abuse and the use of dangerous weapon. The State leaves the amount up to the Court.

BTC: guilty as above. PSI ordered. Modification of bond is granted. Bond to be modified to $1000.00 cash. Additional conditions are NO contact, directly or indirectly with the victim or being present at the location she resides or where she is located. Deft must reside at 1241 Carlisle Ave. May not rent, own, possess or borrow any weapon. The owners of the property of 1241 Carlisle Ave may not have or allow any weapons to come onto their property while defendant resides there. All other terms and conditions as previously ordered remain.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for February 13, 2015 at 10:30 am.
